---

## FEATURE ANATOMY вЂ” MANDATORY

Every feature MUST have ALL files. No exceptions.
If content is not needed yet, generate the file with:
  // No content required for this feature yet
  export {};
NEVER skip creating the file. Consistency is non-negotiable.

```
features/auth/{name}/ or features/app/{name}/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ index.ts          barrel only вЂ” re-exports, zero logic
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ api.ts            API calls + normaliser function
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ hooks.ts          RTK Query hooks or custom hooks
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ types.ts          domain TypeScript interfaces
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ validators.ts     Zod schemas for all forms
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ __tests__/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ api.test.ts
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ hooks.test.ts
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ validators.test.ts
в””в”Ђв”Ђ screens/
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ {ScreenName}/
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ index.tsx         UI only вЂ” thin, 14-step order
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ styles.ts         StyleSheet.create вЂ” theme tokens only
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ skeleton.tsx      full layout skeleton
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ helpers.ts        UI-only helpers
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ __tests__/
        в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ index.test.tsx
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ components/       screen-local components only
            в””в”Ђв”Ђ {ComponentName}/
                в”њв”Ђв”Ђ index.tsx
                в””в”Ђв”Ђ __tests__/
                    в””в”Ђв”Ђ index.test.tsx
```

SM login features (googleLogin, appleLogin, facebookLogin) have no
dedicated screen вЂ” SDK handles UI natively. Use .gitkeep in screens/:
```
features/auth/googleLogin/screens/.gitkeep
```

---

## AUTH FEATURE вЂ” HOW LOGIN COMPOSES SM FEATURES

login/ owns manual login logic + main LoginScreen.
LoginScreen composes all SM login options via SocialLoginButtons component.
Each SM feature is fully isolated вЂ” add or remove with zero impact on others.

```
LoginScreen/index.tsx
    uses в†’ login/hooks.ts          manual login logic
    uses в†’ login/validators.ts     email + password validation
    renders в†’ SocialLoginButtons/  UI component only

SocialLoginButtons/index.tsx
    imports useGoogleLogin   from @features/auth/googleLogin
    imports useAppleLogin    from @features/auth/appleLogin
    imports useFacebookLogin from @features/auth/facebookLogin
    renders Button for each вЂ” analyticsId required on every button
```

Adding a new SM provider (e.g. Twitter):
  1. Create features/auth/twitterLogin/ with full anatomy
  2. Add useTwitterLogin to SocialLoginButtons
  3. Zero changes to login/ or any other feature

Removing a provider:
  1. Delete features/auth/facebookLogin/
  2. Remove from SocialLoginButtons
  3. Zero impact on anything else

---

## SERVICES vs FEATURES вЂ” THE ONLY RULE

```
services/    Pure SDK / infrastructure вЂ” NEVER has a screen
             analytics, crashlytics, sentry, firebase,
             api client, storage, socket, auth-providers SDKs,
             notifications SDK setup (FCM token, channels)

features/    Anything with a screen вЂ” always
             notifications screen в†’ features/app/notifications/
             payments screen     в†’ features/app/payments/
             search screen       в†’ features/app/search/
```

Note: services/notifications/ handles FCM SDK wiring only.
      features/app/notifications/ handles the screen + business logic.
      Both can exist simultaneously вЂ” they serve different concerns.

---

## SCREEN CODE ORDER вЂ” MANDATORY 14 STEPS

Every screen index.tsx follows this exact top-to-bottom order.
Reviewers check order before functionality.

```
1.  Imports          вЂ” external, RN, navigation, internal, styles
2.  Module constants вЂ” PAGE_SIZE, DEBOUNCE_MS вЂ” SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE
3.  Component declaration
4.  useState         вЂ” ALL, grouped by concern, each with intent comment
5.  useRef           вЂ” ALL refs with purpose comment
6.  Redux            вЂ” useDispatch + useSelector
7.  Navigation       вЂ” useNavigation, useRoute, useFocusEffect
8.  Computed values  вЂ” useMemo, useCallback
9.  useEffect        вЂ” one concern per effect, comment header on each
10. Business logic   вЂ” get*, submit*, sort*, validate*, format*
11. Event handlers   вЂ” handle*, on*, toggle*
12. Render helpers   вЂ” render* вЂ” JSX only, zero logic inside
13. Main return      вЂ” single return statement
14. export default   вЂ” at file bottom always
```

---

## NAMING CONVENTIONS

### Feature folders вЂ” always camelCase
```
login, signup, forgotPassword, googleLogin,
appleLogin, facebookLogin, preOnboarding,
dashboard, profile, settings, notifications
```

### Functions
| Prefix   | Purpose                        | Example              |
|----------|--------------------------------|----------------------|
| render   | Returns JSX вЂ” zero logic       | renderBannerItem()   |
| handle   | User interaction handler       | handleLoginPress()   |
| get      | Fetches or retrieves data      | getBanners()         |
| submit   | Posts data to backend          | submitLoginForm()    |
| on       | Event callback prop            | onBannerPress()      |
| format   | Pure data transformation       | formatCurrency()     |
| validate | Returns boolean or error       | validateEmail()      |
| toggle   | Flips a boolean                | toggleModal()        |
| navigate | Handles screen navigation      | navigateToDetail()   |
| sort     | Sorts or filters list          | sortByDate()         |
| set      | Sets local state directly      | setIsLoading()       |

### Files
| Type             | Convention                     | Example                     |
|------------------|--------------------------------|-----------------------------|
| Screen           | PascalCase + Screen            | LoginScreen/index.tsx       |
| Component        | PascalCase noun                | SocialLoginButtons/index.tsx|
| Hook             | use prefix + camelCase         | useGoogleLogin.ts           |
| GraphQL Query    | Get{Resource}.gql.ts           | GetCurrentUser.gql.ts       |
| GraphQL Mutation | {Action}{Resource}.mutation.ts | Login.mutation.ts           |
| GraphQL Fragment | {Resource}Fields.fragment.ts   | UserFields.fragment.ts      |
| Test             | Same name + .test              | LoginScreen.test.tsx        |
| Constants        | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE           | PAGE_SIZE = 20              |

### State declarations
```ts
// CORRECT вЂ” one per line, intent comment required
const [page, setPage]           = useState(1);     // Current page for pagination
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);  // API in-flight state
const [error, setError]         = useState<string | null>(null); // Last error message

// WRONG вЂ” no comments, vague names, multiple per line
const [data,setData]=useState([]);
const [flag,setFlag]=useState(false);
```

---

## IMPORT ORDER вЂ” ALWAYS

```ts
// 1. React
import React, { useState, useCallback } from 'react';

// 2. React Native
import { View, FlatList, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

// 3. External packages
import { useNavigation } from '@react-navigation/native';

// 4. Internal вЂ” features
import { useGoogleLogin }   from '@features/auth/googleLogin';
import { useAppleLogin }    from '@features/auth/appleLogin';
import { useFacebookLogin } from '@features/auth/facebookLogin';

// 5. Internal вЂ” components
import Button   from '@components/ui/Button';
import Skeleton from '@components/feedback/Skeleton';

// 6. Internal вЂ” services
import { logEvent, EVENTS } from '@services/analytics';
import { recordError }      from '@services/crashlytics';

// 7. Internal вЂ” hooks, store, utils, theme, i18n, config
import { useDebounce } from '@hooks/useDebounce';
import { COLORS }      from '@theme/colors';
import { t }           from '@i18n';

// 8. Types
import type { LoginPayload } from '@features/auth/login';

// 9. Styles вЂ” always last
import styles from './styles';
```

---

## ANALYTICS RULES

Every user interaction MUST be tracked. No exceptions.

Button auto-tracks via analyticsId вЂ” no manual call in screen needed.
For non-button interactions, call logEvent manually.

```ts
// Auto-tracked via Button component
<Button
  label="Login"
  onPress={handleLogin}
  analyticsId="login_submit"
  feature="auth"
/>

// Manual for non-button interactions
logEvent({
  name:      EVENTS.MODAL_OPENED,
  screen:    currentScreen,
  feature:   'auth',
  component: 'delete_confirm_modal',
});

// Errors always reported to both Firebase Crashlytics + Sentry
recordError(error as Error, {
  screen:  'LoginScreen',
  feature: 'auth',
  action:  'login_submit',
});
```

---

## API RULES

```ts
// Every feature has a normaliser вЂ” raw API response never reaches components
const normaliseUser = (raw: RawUser): User => ({
  id:        raw._id ?? raw.id,
  firstName: raw.first_name ?? raw.firstName,
  email:     raw.email,
  createdAt: raw.created_at ?? raw.createdAt,
});

// AbortController on every API call in screens
const abortRef = useRef<AbortController | null>(null);
useEffect(() => {
  abortRef.current = new AbortController();
  return () => abortRef.current?.abort();
}, []);
```

---

## GRAPHQL RULES

```ts
// Query: Get{Resource}.gql.ts
export const GET_CURRENT_USER = gql`
  query GetCurrentUser { user { id email firstName } }
`;

// Mutation: {Action}{Resource}.mutation.ts
export const LOGIN = gql`
  mutation Login($input: LoginInput!) { login(input: $input) { token user { id } } }
`;

// Apollo hooks ALWAYS wrapped in feature hooks вЂ” never used directly in screens
export const useLogin = () => {
  const [loginMutation, { loading }] = useMutation(LOGIN);
  const submitLogin = async (input: LoginPayload) => {
    const result = await loginMutation({ variables: { input } });
    return result.data?.login;
  };
  return { submitLogin, loading };
};
```

---

## TESTING RULES

```ts
// Always factory functions вЂ” never inline test objects
const makeUser = (overrides: Partial<User> = {}): User => ({
  id: 'user-1', email: 'test@example.com',
  firstName: 'Test', lastName: 'User',
  createdAt: '2025-01-01T00:00:00Z',
  ...overrides,
});

// Mock one layer below the file under test
// In api.test.ts вЂ” mock the HTTP client
jest.mock('@services/api/client');

// In hooks.test.ts вЂ” mock the api module
jest.mock('@features/auth/login/api');

// No .only or .skip in committed test files вЂ” blocks CI
```

Coverage thresholds:
  utils/ validators/:    100%
  services/ api/:        90%
  features/ components/: 80%
  screens/:              80%

---

## NEW FEATURE GENERATION вЂ” CHECKLIST

Ask these if not specified:
1. Feature name?
2. Auth flow (pre-login) or App flow (post-login)?
3. REST or GraphQL or both?
4. List screen + detail screen, or one screen?
5. Needs form/validation?
6. Connects to which store slices?

Then generate in this exact order:
1.  features/{flow}/{name}/types.ts
2.  features/{flow}/{name}/validators.ts
3.  features/{flow}/{name}/api.ts
4.  features/{flow}/{name}/hooks.ts
5.  features/{flow}/{name}/index.ts
6.  features/{flow}/{name}/__tests__/validators.test.ts
7.  features/{flow}/{name}/__tests__/api.test.ts
8.  features/{flow}/{name}/__tests__/hooks.test.ts
9.  features/{flow}/{name}/screens/{Name}Screen/index.tsx
10. features/{flow}/{name}/screens/{Name}Screen/styles.ts
11. features/{flow}/{name}/screens/{Name}Screen/skeleton.tsx
12. features/{flow}/{name}/screens/{Name}Screen/helpers.ts
13. features/{flow}/{name}/screens/{Name}Screen/__tests__/index.test.tsx

---

## ABSOLUTE FORBIDDEN PATTERNS

```
NO any type
NO inline styles вЂ” use styles.ts with theme tokens
NO hardcoded colors or strings вЂ” use theme + i18n
NO cross-feature imports вЂ” features communicate via store only
NO console.log вЂ” use analytics logger
NO ScrollView + .map() for lists вЂ” always FlatList
NO full objects as navigation params вЂ” IDs only
NO tokens in AsyncStorage вЂ” keychain only
NO API calls inside screen index.tsx вЂ” hooks only
NO .only or .skip in committed tests
NO hardcoded API URLs вЂ” use config/env.ts
NO PII in analytics events (no email, phone, name)
NO logic inside render* functions вЂ” JSX only
NO screens inside services/
NO SDK setup inside features/
```

---

## RESPONSE FORMAT

Always respond as:

```
Creating X files for [feature/component name]:

src/features/auth/googleLogin/types.ts
src/features/auth/googleLogin/api.ts
... list all files first ...

--- src/features/auth/googleLogin/types.ts ---
[complete file content]

--- src/features/auth/googleLogin/api.ts ---
[complete file content]

TODOs (manual steps required):
- [ ] Add GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_ID to .env files
- [ ] Register googleLogin in AuthNavigator if needed
- [ ] Add google_login button to SocialLoginButtons component
```

Complete files always. Never partial. Never pseudocode.
Ask one focused question if a requirement is unclear before generating.

---

## FINAL RULE

If it is not in this file, it does not ship.
Every file generated must look like it was written by the same engineer.
Consistency across 1 file or 100 files is the same standard.
When in doubt вЂ” ask one question, then generate.
